<paragraph blockId="5.[317,1270,436,544]" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">
surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[415,500,436,457]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1675,1696]" captionTargetBox="[351,1238,426,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[349,1238,424,1646]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–8. Leptocera austroafricana sp. n., male postabdomen. 1 = subepandrial sclerite, cercus and contours of posterior part of surstylus, caudal view, 2 = sternite 5 and sternite 6, 3 = contours of sternite 5 and synsternite 6–8, caudal view, 4 = phallus and phallapodeme, left lateral view, 5 = caudal part of sternite 5, ventral view, 6 = postgonite, left lateral view, 7 = anterior and posterior part of surstylus, lateral view, 8 = hypandrium,ventral view.Scale bars:0.4 mm for Figs 2–3 (upper bar), 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735890/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Figs 1, 7</figureCitation>
) with apical bristle only half as long as body of the surstylus. Postgonite (
<figureCitation box="[1205,1263,436,457]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1675,1696]" captionTargetBox="[351,1238,426,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[349,1238,424,1646]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–8. Leptocera austroafricana sp. n., male postabdomen. 1 = subepandrial sclerite, cercus and contours of posterior part of surstylus, caudal view, 2 = sternite 5 and sternite 6, 3 = contours of sternite 5 and synsternite 6–8, caudal view, 4 = phallus and phallapodeme, left lateral view, 5 = caudal part of sternite 5, ventral view, 6 = postgonite, left lateral view, 7 = anterior and posterior part of surstylus, lateral view, 8 = hypandrium,ventral view.Scale bars:0.4 mm for Figs 2–3 (upper bar), 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735890/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) with extremely long but not broad basal part, which has a posteroventral process. Apical part of postgonite slender with curved apex. Phallus 
<quantity box="[752,837,494,515]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
long with a strong melanised dorsal rib (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1675,1696]" captionTargetBox="[351,1238,426,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[349,1238,424,1646]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–8. Leptocera austroafricana sp. n., male postabdomen. 1 = subepandrial sclerite, cercus and contours of posterior part of surstylus, caudal view, 2 = sternite 5 and sternite 6, 3 = contours of sternite 5 and synsternite 6–8, caudal view, 4 = phallus and phallapodeme, left lateral view, 5 = caudal part of sternite 5, ventral view, 6 = postgonite, left lateral view, 7 = anterior and posterior part of surstylus, lateral view, 8 = hypandrium,ventral view.Scale bars:0.4 mm for Figs 2–3 (upper bar), 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735890/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Phallapodeme (
<figureCitation box="[501,561,523,544]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="4.[317,360,1675,1696]" captionTargetBox="[351,1238,426,1644]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[349,1238,424,1646]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1–8. Leptocera austroafricana sp. n., male postabdomen. 1 = subepandrial sclerite, cercus and contours of posterior part of surstylus, caudal view, 2 = sternite 5 and sternite 6, 3 = contours of sternite 5 and synsternite 6–8, caudal view, 4 = phallus and phallapodeme, left lateral view, 5 = caudal part of sternite 5, ventral view, 6 = postgonite, left lateral view, 7 = anterior and posterior part of surstylus, lateral view, 8 = hypandrium,ventral view.Scale bars:0.4 mm for Figs 2–3 (upper bar), 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735890/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) much longer than hypandrial apodeme.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735892" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5735892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735892/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" startId="5.[317,359,1693,1714]" targetBox="[318,1266,602,1636]" targetPageId="5">
