, 
<quantity box="[811,884,1808,1829]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="230" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
for 
<figureCitation box="[925,1068,1808,1829]" captionStart="Figs 9–16" captionStartId="5.[317,359,1693,1714]" captionTargetBox="[318,1266,602,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[317,1269,602,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 9–16. Leptocera spp., female postabdomen and spermathecae. 9–12. L. austroafricana sp. n.: 9 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 10 = tergite 8, lateral view, 11 = sternite 8, ventral view, 12 = spermathecae. 13–16. L. elgonensis RICHARDS: 13 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 14 = tergite 8, lateral view, 15 = spermathecae, 16 = sternite 7 and sternite 8, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735892/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="230">Figs 11–12, 15</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1270,436,601]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">
Female tergite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[549,619,436,457]" captionStart="Figs 9–16" captionStartId="5.[317,359,1693,1714]" captionTargetBox="[318,1266,602,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[317,1269,602,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 9–16. Leptocera spp., female postabdomen and spermathecae. 9–12. L. austroafricana sp. n.: 9 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 10 = tergite 8, lateral view, 11 = sternite 8, ventral view, 12 = spermathecae. 13–16. L. elgonensis RICHARDS: 13 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 14 = tergite 8, lateral view, 15 = spermathecae, 16 = sternite 7 and sternite 8, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) with rather few setae on dorsal half, ventral half with medium-long setae only. Sternite 8 (
<figureCitation box="[528,596,465,486]" captionStart="Figs 9–16" captionStartId="5.[317,359,1693,1714]" captionTargetBox="[318,1266,602,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[317,1269,602,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 9–16. Leptocera spp., female postabdomen and spermathecae. 9–12. L. austroafricana sp. n.: 9 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 10 = tergite 8, lateral view, 11 = sternite 8, ventral view, 12 = spermathecae. 13–16. L. elgonensis RICHARDS: 13 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 14 = tergite 8, lateral view, 15 = spermathecae, 16 = sternite 7 and sternite 8, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) with a broad but short posteromedial lamella and with 2 pairs of short caudal setulae. Tergite 10 completely fused with cerci (
<figureCitation box="[852,911,494,515]" captionStart="Figs 9–16" captionStartId="5.[317,359,1693,1714]" captionTargetBox="[318,1266,602,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[317,1269,602,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 9–16. Leptocera spp., female postabdomen and spermathecae. 9–12. L. austroafricana sp. n.: 9 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 10 = tergite 8, lateral view, 11 = sternite 8, ventral view, 12 = spermathecae. 13–16. L. elgonensis RICHARDS: 13 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 14 = tergite 8, lateral view, 15 = spermathecae, 16 = sternite 7 and sternite 8, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), with a pair of medium-long seta on tergal part and with a longer pair of setae on cercal part. Spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1080,523,544]" captionStart="Figs 9–16" captionStartId="5.[317,359,1693,1714]" captionTargetBox="[318,1266,602,1636]" captionTargetId="figure-70@5.[317,1269,602,1641]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 9–16. Leptocera spp., female postabdomen and spermathecae. 9–12. L. austroafricana sp. n.: 9 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 10 = tergite 8, lateral view, 11 = sternite 8, ventral view, 12 = spermathecae. 13–16. L. elgonensis RICHARDS: 13 = tergite 10 fused with cerci, dorsal view, 14 = tergite 8, lateral view, 15 = spermathecae, 16 = sternite 7 and sternite 8, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5735892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5735892/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) very characteristic with very long sclerotised ducts; shape oval, unpaired spermatheca sub-globular, all the three spermathecae with thin apically curved spicules on most of their surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[317,1269,638,688]" pageId="6" pageNumber="231">Etymology. The specific epithet (“south African”) of the new species refers to its occurrence in the southern half of Africa.</paragraph>
